Hajiya A’isha, the mother of Secretary to the Government of Katsina State (SSG), Alhaji Mustapha Muhammad Inuwa, has died. Hajiya A’isha, popularly known as Hajiya Ta-Mashi, aged 91, died on Sunday, living behind four children and 36 grandchildren. Governor Aminu Masari through a statement issued his spokesman, Alhaji Abdu Labaran, described the death of Hajiya A’isha as a great loss to her family and the state. He prayed to Allah to forgive her sins, grant her Aljannah Firdausi (Paradise) and give the family the fortitude to bear the loss. Bauchi PDP chieftain donates 9 motorcycles for empowerment Lagos police arrests notorious Berry Boys’ Supreme Cult… Police pledges to rescue former ABU VC’s daughter Gov. Oyetola congratulates Fayemi at 55 ALSO READ: Bauchi PDP chieftain donates 9 motorcycles for empowerment The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the funeral prayer for the deceased was conducted at the GRA Katsina Juma’at Mosque. NAN also reports that the funeral prayer was attended by Governor Masari, Emir of Daura Alhaji Faruq Umar and Director-General of NIMET, Prof. Sani Abubakar Mashi. Others were Commissioner of Water Resources, Alhaji Musa Adamu Funtua, other members of the State Executive Council and top government officials. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.